Teen executed in 1944 may have been innocent

03:04
  • Share this —

George Stinney, Jr. was 14 years old when South Carolina executed him in 1944, making him the youngest person executed in the U.S. in the 20th century. He was convicted of murdering two girls. Now there's a move to clear his name. NBC’s Mark Potter reports.Oct. 5, 2011
